dc_title_s: Shelby County, Iowa, 1955, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet label. Image is a photoreduction of the mosaic created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BKR. Form of individual image numbering: BKR-1P-[number], BKR-2P-[number], or BKM-3P-[number]."Flying completed 9-1-55" Flown by Puckett Aerial Surveys, Inc. Louisville, Kentucky. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
